Wow! What a difference!!
Very pleased with this company!
That is real customer service!
Will comeback again!! ðŸ˜Š

The food is delicious, but the employee who makes the crepes ( a lady with fake eyelashes and a tattoo  with two swords on her right arm is very unpleasant, she works like she hates the job, she doesn't  even look at  anybody when she calls out the number for the food pick up.
Terrible service!!

August 22, 6:30 am.

Here  I am again. At this location for breakfast at the airport before my flight.
I order a crepe , and a very short  guy ( the voice was a little feminine, so it could be a girl with very short haircut) , calls my number â€œ 159â€ and placed my crepe on the counter, and continue to look down. The food is delicious at Three Twins, but I refuse to spend $13.27 for a single crepe and have bad service.</Review>

<review>Meh. Seeing how the company came from Petaluma which is near and dear to my heart since I grew up so close to this town and spent many-a-night traveling through, I had high expectations.

The ice-cream is good. Flavors... they could do a little better. The PBC3 (peanut butter cookie confetti crunch) is pretty dang good but even though the names of each flavor titillate you, the actual ingredients lack substance. The certified organic aspect brings new light to the message of what this company is trying to provide, but these days who isn't organic?

I think Three Twins can do a little better and get out of the box a little bit.</review></record>

<rate>5<//rate><text>I rarely take the time to post reviews; however,  Dan and his business are well deserving of this review.

First of, finding an honest and dependable mechanic nowadays is extremely rare.  Between my family and I, we utilize 6 cars; therefore, I truly believe in preventative maintenance, and have dealt with many auto services shops.

I learned about TLD Auto Service after purchasing a 1998 Lexus ES 300.  I purchased the Lexus for commuting purposes.  As many of us do, I jumped on Google and searched for a mechanic who specialized in Lexus.  This is where I learned of TLD.  I read the reviews and decided to give TLD the opportunity to service my Lexus.

I met Dan for the first time when dropping of the Lexus for service.  This was the first Lexus I had owned; however, Dan gave me an educational class on my Lexus.  Not many mechanics will take the time to do this.  Time is money!  Right?  Well, with Dan, I learned he also wants you ( the customer) to know the ins/outs of your car.  I left the Lexus with Dan for the completion of a major service.

The major service took about 2 days considering the delivery of parts.  When I picked up the car,  the first thing I noticed was that my Lexus was washed and interior clean.  The exterior of my Lexus was extremely dirty when I had initially dropped it off.

I stepped into Dan's Office and he stated, "Hey, help yourself to anything you want in the fridge."  It was hot, so I took him up on his offer and made a selection from various drinks.

Shortly after, Dan took me outside to my Lexus and went over the work he had completed.  I was sold when he showed me (and later texted me) pictures (before and after) of the work he had completed.

After a tour of my car, we went to Dan's Office where I payed the bill for his service.  Although I will not disclose the amount, I was surprised at the amount due based on all the work he had completed.  Dan took the time to explain each service completed.  I truly was expecting to pay much more based on previous experiences.  Dan's price was beyond reasonable.

As I previously stated, my family operates 6 vehicles, which not all are Lexus or Toyota; however, the vehicles that are, I always call Dan for services and he is able to accommodate me.  I ONLY WISH HE SPECIALIZED IN OTHER MAKES!!!

In summary, if you own a Lexus or Toyota, and are looking for an honest and reliable autoshop to perform quality service, I highly recommmend TLD Auto Service.

<Review>I rarely take the time to post reviews; however,  Dan and his business are well deserving of this review.

First of, finding an honest and dependable mechanic nowadays is extremely rare.  Between my family and I, we utilize 6 cars; therefore, I truly believe in preventative maintenance, and have dealt with many auto services shops.

I learned about TLD Auto Service after purchasing a 1998 Lexus ES 300.  I purchased the Lexus for commuting purposes.  As many of us do, I jumped on Google and searched for a mechanic who specialized in Lexus.  This is where I learned of TLD.  I read the reviews and decided to give TLD the opportunity to service my Lexus.

I met Dan for the first time when dropping of the Lexus for service.  This was the first Lexus I had owned; however, Dan gave me an educational class on my Lexus. I left the Lexus with Dan for the completion of a major service.

The major service took about 2 days considering the delivery of parts.  When I picked up the car,  the first thing I noticed was that my Lexus was washed and interior clean.  The exterior of my Lexus was extremely dirty when I had initially dropped it off.

< Text>
I was on a family trip to Sequoia National Park, when my Toyota Sienna broke down. Thank god I found Dan from TLD. He was able to take the car in right away and meticulously examined every single part of the car. He located the problem and immediately placed an order for parts from a quality factory. I appreciated that he had experience working with Toyota and Lexus directly for over 12 years. Let me just say he does not skip steps, cut corners, or use cheap parts. His craftsmanship is impeccable and his attention to detail is impressive. Although it was an older family car, he treated it with the utmost respect and care as if it was his own child. We ended up renting a car so we could continue our family trip. Throughout the trip, I would get continuous updates from Dan via text. He was very communicative every step of the way. The shop was closed the day we returned from our trip and Dan went out of his way to open the store and accommodate us. When I received the final bill, I was given an itemized receipt with line by line details along with accompanying photos. Everything was done with honesty and integrity so I did not once feel cheated. He even washed the car for me! Post-trip I would get follow up texts from Dan to ensure everything was still running smoothly. A few months later, I had a minor problem (completely separate from what Dan fixed) and texted Dan. He, of course, responded back immediately and talked me through my options.

This is the first time I have ever left a review for an auto shop because I think this is an outstanding small business and Dan is an incredible business owner. I only wish I lived closer so that all of my cars can get the TLD treatment.<//Text>

<rating>5<//rating><Review>Once a month I travel from Southern California to a beautiful foothill community in Northern California.  I was a little over 2 and 1/2 hours into a 7 hour trip at 6:30 am on a Saturday when the Check Engine warning light and two other warning lights started flashing on my 2001 Lexus with nearly 236,000 miles on it.  I was 10 miles south of Tulare but decided to risk reaching Tulare to pull over for breakfast and to search for a Toyota/Lexus service shop.  The first entry on Google Search was TLD Auto Service, another 20 minutes away, and it was the only service shop that would be open on Saturday.  The nearest Lexus dealership is 50 miles away in Fresno.  I decided to risk the trip to TLD in Visalia knowing that if I broke down I could get AAA to tow me to TLD.  I made it there by 7:45 and put a call into the shop--no answer, but I left a message pleading my predicament.  At just past 8:30 Dan showed up with a smile on his face and his hand extended in greeting.  Dan is simply an absolutely delightful man.  He completely put me at ease while solving my problem and he patiently and thoroughly explained what had gone wrong and how to fix it.  He also performed a thorough check of the entire vehicle and pointed out to me what was right and what was wrong with the prior service that had been performed on the car.  He even convinced me that with proper service my car can easily make 400,000 miles.  I spent nearly 4 hours with Dan while he worked giving my car a thorough tune-up--sharing backgrounds (somehow I reminded him of his biology teacher in high school!?!), talking about family, hearing about his journey from San Jose to Visalia to provide the best life for his family, but most importantly hearing about his mantra for providing the absolute best service for his clients.  He will only use OEM parts, he will only charge a fair price, he will always thoroughly explain (and demonstrate through photographic documentation) what needs to be fixed on the vehicle.  As I will still be making round trips just past Visalia twice a month I will be booking appointments with Dan for him to perform all of the maintenance work on my Lexus.  He is so considerate that he offered to essentially chauffeur me (and my wife) to a nearby restaurant while we wait for the service to be performed.
